 MiB: Ted Seides, Capital Allocators https://ritholtz.com/2023/08/mib-ted-seides/Barry Ritholtz Sat, 12 Aug 2023 14:30:14 +0000 Active ManagementAlternatives/PE/Hedge FundsMiB https://ritholtz.com/?p=318192 <p> This week, we speak with asset management expert Ted Seides, founder of Capital Allocators. His most recent book is “Capital Allocators: How the world&#39;s elite money managers lead and invest;” he is also the host of the popular “Capital Allocators” podcast, which reached 16 million downloads in June. Seides is a CFA charterholder and has…</p><p><a class="button" href="https://ritholtz.com/2023/08/mib-ted-seides/">阅读更多<i class="icon ion-arrow-right-c"></i></a></p><p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://ritholtz.com/2023/08/mib-ted-seides/">MiB: Ted Seides, Capital Allocators</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://ritholtz.com">The Big Picture</a> .</p> ; <p><iframe style="width: 100%; max-width: 660px; overflow: hidden; border-radius: 10px;" src="https://embed.podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/ted-seides-on-the-worlds-elite-money-managers/id730188152?i=1000624176555" height="175" frameborder="0" sandbox="allow-forms allow-popups allow-same-origin allow-scripts allow-storage-access-by-user-activation allow-top-navigation-by-user-activation"></iframe></p><p></p><p> This week, we speak with asset management expert <a href="https://twitter.com/tseides" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Ted Seides</a> , founder of <a href="https://www.capitalallocators.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Capital Allocators</a> . His most recent book is “ <a href="https://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0857198866/thebigpictu09-20" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Capital Allocators: How the world&#39;s elite money managers lead and invest</a> ;” he is also the host of the popular “ <a href="https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/capital-allocators-inside-the-institutional/id1223764016" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Capital Allocators” podcast</a> , which reached 16 million downloads in June. Seides is a CFA charterholder and has an MBA from Harvard Business School.</p><p> He studied with David Swensen as an undergrad at Yale, and his first job was working for Swensen at the Yale endowment. What we now call the “Yale Model” was invested in stocks and bonds but also venture capital, hedge funds, real estate, timber, commodities, etc. before most market participants had considered those kinds of assets. As early as 1992, Yale&#39;s Endowment had a robust portfolio of venture capital and hedge funds, long before it became popular. He also explains why the post-financial crisis era has been so challenging for alternatives, and why the S&amp;P 500 is not the proper benchmark for most.</p><p> It was a lot of fun listening to Seides explain how his infamous bet with Warren Buffett came about. As well known as this bet was — Hedge Funds vs S&amp;P 500 — the background was quite amazing and his back and forth with Buffett led to a wonderful experience.</p><p> At 14 months into the bet, his pool of funds was up 50%. Buffett would note at the annual meeting, at the end of the morning session, by saying, “ <em>I am losing the bet, let&#39;s go to lunch</em> .” Slowly but surely over the next 6 years, the market caught up.</p><p> Seides says the entire experience was utterly delightful. He and his colleagues ended up having annual dinners with Buffett, each of which was unique and wonderful. One of the dinners included Morgan Stanley CIO Steve Galbraith, who was friends with Jack Bogle. The result was Buffett got to host Bogle at the Berkshire Hathaway annual meeting.</p><p> A list of his favorite books <a href="https://ritholtz.com/2023/08/mib-ted-seides/#more-318192">is here</a> ; A transcript of our conversation is <a href="https://ritholtz.com/2023/08/transcript-ted-seides/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">available here</a> Tuesday.</p><p>您可以在<a href="https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/ted-seides-on-the-worlds-elite-money-managers/id730188152?i=1000624176555" target="_blank" rel="noopener">iTunes</a> 、 <a href="https://open.spotify.com/episode/2h703TgVtK60lpMrWYGiNS" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Spotify</a> 、 <a href="https://www.stitcher.com/show/masters-in-business" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Stitcher</a> 、 <a href="https://podcasts.google.com/feed/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cub21ueWNvbnRlbnQuY29tL2QvcGxheWxpc3QvZTczYzk5OGUtNmU2MC00MzJmLTg2MTAtYWUyMTAxNDBjNWIxLzRlNGNkOTEwLTQwYTEtNDYxOS1hNWYzLWFlMmIwMDEyZmZmZi81ODczYTNjYi0yOThmLTQwYmMtYjcxZi1hZTJiMDAxMzAwMGQvcG9kY2FzdC5yc3M" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google</a> 、 <a href="https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLe4PRejZgr0PzN7r8NikAnOqP70DHhoJ0" target="_blank" rel="noopener">YouTube</a>和<a href="http://www.bloomberg.com/podcasts/masters-in-business/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Bloomberg 上流</a>式传输和下载我们的完整对话，包括任何播客附加内容。您可以<a class="gtrackexternal" href="https://plnk.to/MIB?to=page">在此处找到</a>您最喜欢的播客主机上的所有早期播客。</p><p>请务必在下周与法律学者卡斯·桑斯坦（Cass Sunstein）一起查看我们的<a href="https://ritholtz.com/category/podcast/mib/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" data-web-url="http://www.bloombergview.com/topics/masters-in-business">商业硕士课程</a>，他创立并领导了哈佛法学院行为经济学和公共政策项目。他撰写了多本书，包括畅销书《 <a href="https://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0300122233/thebigpictu09-20" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>助推：改善有关健康、财富和幸福的决策</em></a>》。 （与诺贝尔奖获得者理查德·塞勒合着）和《纽约时报》畅销书《 <a href="https://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0062484222/thebigpictu09-20" target="_blank" rel="noopener">星球大战中的世界</a>》。他的新书是《 <a href="https://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/1009400460/thebigpictu09-20" target="_blank" rel="noopener">关于决策的决策：日常生活中的实践理性</a>》。</p><div></div><p><span id="more-318192"></span></p><p></p><h3> Ted Seides Authored Books</h3><p> <strong><a href="https://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0857198866/thebigpictu09-20" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Capital Allocators: How the world&#39;s elite money managers lead and invest</a></strong> by Ted Seides<br /> <a href="https://www.amazon.com/e